19/10/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU President Herman van Rompuy begins a tour of the Balkans on Tuesday (October 19th) with stops in Macedonia and Montenegro.
In a message issued Monday, he said that Europe is committed to the prospects of the Western Balkans, and called on countries in the region to continue their fight against corruption and organised crime and to co-operate with The Hague war crimes tribunal.
Van Rompuy also plans to visit Bosnia and Herzegovina and Albania.
(MIA, Makfax, RTCG, Radio Free Europe, B92 - 18/10/10)
